 Port Elizabeth - Police in Motherwell, Port Elizabeth, have appealed to the public to assist with information that can help them locate a missing 11-year old boy, Siyahluma Moss. Moss was reported missing to police on Monday night at 20:00. "He was last seen on Monday, at 07:00, when he left home to go to school, but never returned home," said police spokesperson, Captain Andre Beetge. "He lives with his grandmother in Mokgatho Street in NU10, Motherwell, and attends school at Nxanelwi Mfundo Primary School. "On further investigation, it was found that Siyahluma never attended school, but he left for school dressed in school uniform with yellow shirt, grey pants and black jersey." He said that any person that can assist police in finding the boy can contact detective Warrant Officer Riaan Smith at 071 352 5094 or 08600 10111. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 